[
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"281383\">Richard Feldman</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/formatting.20space.20in.20static.20dispatch/near/502796631\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>an easy fix would be changing accessor syntax to be <code>_.b</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Should field access be unique or should we generalize this to \"a single underscore in an expression is sugar for <code>unique_name</code> with an expression prefix of <code>|unique_name|</code>\"?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">bar</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">bar</span><span class=\"p\">())</span>\n\n<span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">bar</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">baz</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">bar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">bar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 502875491,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1740932326
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't want to scope creep into that</p>",
        "id": 502877410,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1740933646
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Scala does this and it would be a very big change to how Roc code looks - the last two examples there being the tip of the iceberg</p>",
        "id": 502877638,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1740933790
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>this is the sort of feature that needs to start with a specific pain point, like \"______ feels painful to read, and something like <code>_</code> would make it a lot nicer to read\" and then we can weigh that upside against the downsides <span aria-label=\"big smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"big smile\">:big_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 502882137,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1740936817
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>because I don't think consistency is enough of a reason to do this</p>",
        "id": 502882175,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1740936841
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, this feature has definitely been ask for and pushed back against for anonymous lambdas before.</p>",
        "id": 502887479,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1740940519
    }
